{
  "texts": [
    "We present retrieval results on the MultiHop-RAG dataset in Table 1.",
    "Question decomposition (QD) and reranking (RR) individually improve recall-oriented metrics: QD yields +4.4 percentage points on Hits@4 and +2.9 on Hits@10, while RR achieves a +7.6 point gain on Hits@4.",
    "Reranking also substantially improves MAP@10 and MRR@10.",
    "Our proposed pipeline, which combines both modules (QD+RR), achieves the strongest results overall, reaching 87.2% Hits@10 and 0.635 MRR@10.",
    "For comparison, the strongest configurations in the original MultiHop-RAG paper (Tang and Yang, 2024), which use text-ada-002 (OpenAI, 2022) and voyage-02 (Voyage AI Innovations Inc., 2024) embeddings with bge-reranker-large reranker."
  ]
}